        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 12:52PM PDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 1251 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Basque Station, or 27 miles south of Rome, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
